# Environment Variables for Railway Deployment

## Dashboard Service
NEXT_PUBLIC_N8N_BASE_URL=https://your-n8n-service.up.railway.app/webhook

## n8n Service
N8N_BASIC_AUTH_ACTIVE=true
N8N_BASIC_AUTH_USER=admin
N8N_BASIC_AUTH_PASSWORD=CHANGE_THIS_PASSWORD
WEBHOOK_URL=https://your-n8n-service.up.railway.app
N8N_HOST=0.0.0.0
N8N_PORT=5678
N8N_PROTOCOL=https
NODE_ENV=production

# PostgreSQL (Railway will auto-inject these)
DB_TYPE=postgresdb
DB_POSTGRESDB_HOST=${{Postgres.RAILWAY_PRIVATE_DOMAIN}}
DB_POSTGRESDB_PORT=5432
DB_POSTGRESDB_DATABASE=${{Postgres.PGDATABASE}}
DB_POSTGRESDB_USER=${{Postgres.PGUSER}}
DB_POSTGRESDB_PASSWORD=${{Postgres.PGPASSWORD}}

# MongoDB Atlas
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://artechnical707_db_user:NiGA7hwIIUjgXWiD@rtgsai.pjyqjep.mongodb.net/

## AI Service
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://artechnical707_db_user:NiGA7hwIIUjgXWiD@rtgsai.pjyqjep.mongodb.net/
PORT=8000

## Telegram Bot
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=YOUR_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN_HERE

---

## Instructions:

1. Copy the relevant variables for each service
2. In Railway dashboard, go to each service
3. Click "Variables" tab
4. Add each environment variable
5. Replace placeholder values:
   - CHANGE_THIS_PASSWORD → Strong password
   - YOUR_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN_HERE → Your actual bot token
   - your-n8n-service.up.railway.app → Your actual Railway domain

## Important Notes:

- Railway auto-generates domains like: servicename-production.up.railway.app
- Update NEXT_PUBLIC_N8N_BASE_URL after n8n is deployed
- PostgreSQL variables are auto-injected by Railway (use ${{Postgres.XXX}} syntax)
- MongoDB Atlas IP whitelist: Add 0.0.0.0/0 to allow Railway connections
